<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 2. Male left palp of the holotype of Clubiona jiugong sp. nov. A. Prolateral view; B. Rretrolateral view; C. Bulb, prolateral view; D. Bulb, ventral view; E. Bulb, retrolateral view. Abbreviations: C = conductor; E = embolus; EP = embolar part; EPA = embolar part apophysis; RTA = retrolateral tibial apophysis; ST = subtegulum. Scale bars: 0.1 mm (equal for A and B, equal for C-E)." , "Figure 1. Clubiona jiugong sp. nov. A. Distribution record (red circles); B. Male holotype; C. Male left palp of the holotype, ventral view. Abbreviations: C = conductor; E = embolus; EP = embolar part; EPA = embolar part apophysis; RTA = retrolateral tibial apophysis; ST = subtegulum. Scale bar: 0.1 mm (C). The photograph of the living spider was provided by Qianle Lu (Shenzhen, Guangdong)." , "Figure 3. Clubiona jiugong sp. nov., female paratype and male holotype. A. Intact epigyne, ventral view; B. Cleared epigyne, ventral view; C. Cleared vulva, dorsal view; D. Vulva, cleared and embedded in Arabic gum, dorsal view; E. Male habitus, dorsal view; F. Male habitus, lateral view; G. Female habitus, dorsal view; H. Female habitus, ventral view. Abbreviations: BS = bursa; CD = copulatory duct; CO = copulatory opening; H = hood; SP = spermatheca. Scale bars: 0.1 mm (equal for A-D); 1 mm (equal for E and F, equal for G and H)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/511634" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/534389" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/511635" .

